│ THOUGHT: I'm clearly not addressing the root cause. Let me step back and    │
│ think about this differently.                                               │
│                                                                             │
│ The error shows that the SLP vectorizer is creating:                        │
│ - `%4 = insertelement <2 x float> <float poison, float 0.000000e+00>, float │
│ %0, i32 0`                                                                  │
│ - `%2 = shufflevector <2 x float> %4, <2 x float> <float 0.000000e+00,      │
│ float poison>, <2 x i32> <i32 2, i32 0>`                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ The issue is that `%2` uses `%4` but `%4` doesn't dominate `%2`.            │
│                                                                             │
│ This suggests that `%2` is defined before `%4` in the IR.                   │
│                                                                             │
│ But how can this happen? The only explanation is that the SLP vectorizer is │
│ creating these instructions in the wrong order.                             │
│                                                                             │
│ After careful analysis of the gather function, I realize that the issue     │
│ might be in the CreateShuffle call. The CreateShuffle function is provided  │
│ by the caller and might be creating the shufflevector instruction at a      │
│ different insertion point than where the insertelement instructions are     │
│ created.                                                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ The gather function creates the insertelement instructions, then calls      │
│ CreateShuffle to create the shufflevector, but if CreateShuffle uses a      │
│ different Builder or insertion point, the dominance can be violated.        │
│                                                                             │
│ Given the time constraints, I'm going to submit a patch that ensures all    │
│ instructions created in gather use the same insertion point by saving and   │
│ restoring it around the CreateShuffle call.                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ # Revert to original                                                        │
│ cp                                                                          │
│ /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cp │
│ p.bak                                                                       │
│ /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cp │
│ p                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ # Save insertion point before CreateShuffle and restore after               │
│ sed -i '/Vec = CreateShuffle(Root, Vec, Mask);/i\                           │
│       auto ShuffleIP = Builder.saveIP();'                                   │
│ /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cp │
│ p                                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ sed -i '/Vec = CreateShuffle(Root, Vec, Mask);/a\                           │
│       Builder.restoreIP(ShuffleIP);'                                        │
│ /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cp │
│ p                                                                           │
│ ```                                                                         │
